<p><a name="Italy" id="Italy"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Black_Madonna&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Italy">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Italy</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Our Lady of <a href="/wiki/Tindari" title="Tindari">Tindari</a>, Sicily</li>
<li>Black Madonna of Oropa, <a href="/wiki/Piedmont" title="Piedmont">Piedmont</a></li>
<li>Our Lady of Crea, <a href="/wiki/Casale_Monferrato" title="Casale Monferrato">Casale Monferrato</a>, <a href="/wiki/Province_of_Alessandria" title="Province of Alessandria">Alessandria</a>. In the hillside Sanctuary at Crea (Santuario di Crea), a cedar-wood figure, said to be one of three Black Virgins brought to Italy from the <a href="/wiki/Holy_Land" title="Holy Land">Holy Land</a> c<a href="/wiki/345" title="345">345</a> by <a href="/wiki/Eusebius_of_Alexandria" title="Eusebius of Alexandria">St. Eusebius</a>.</li>
<li>Madonna della Salute, <a href="/wiki/Santa_Maria_della_Salute" title="Santa Maria della Salute">Santa Maria della Salute</a>, Venice</li>
<li>Madonna di Canneto, Canneto Valley near <a href="/wiki/Settefrati" title="Settefrati">Settefrati</a>, <a href="/wiki/Province_of_Frosinone" title="Province of Frosinone">Province of Frosinone</a>, Lazio</li>
<li>Madonna in the Church of San Prospero. Faeto, Province of Foggia in the Puglia Region.</li>
<li>Madonna di <a href="/wiki/Viggiano" title="Viggiano">Viggiano</a>, <a href="/wiki/Basilicata" title="Basilicata">Basilicata</a></li>
</ul>
